âœ… What is a Gateway Runner?

A gateway runner is:
	â€¢	A proxy endpoint created by your DevOps/Infra team
	â€¢	It receives API calls from GitHub Actions
	â€¢	It authenticates/validates the request
	â€¢	It triggers Bamboo internally behind the firewall
	â€¢	GitHub never calls Bamboo directly

âœ” Why companies use it:
	â€¢	Bamboo is usually on-prem, not public
	â€¢	GitHub cannot reach internal networks
	â€¢	The gateway runner acts as a bridge

