ğŸŸ¦ Current GitHub Workflow Using Gateway Runner

â¤ Repo A: .github/workflows/release.yml

name: Trigger Bamboo via Gateway Runner

on:
  release:
    types: [published]

jobs:
  trigger-bamboo:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Trigger Gateway Runner
        run: |
          VERSION=${{ github.event.release.tag_name }}

          curl -X POST \
            -H "Authorization: Bearer ${{ secrets.GATEWAY_TOKEN }}" \
            -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
            https://gateway.company.com/run-bamboo \
            -d "{\"plan\": \"PROJECT-PLAN\", \"version\": \"$VERSION\"}"

Required Secret:
	â€¢	GATEWAY_TOKEN â€” a token provided by DevOps team for the gateway runner.

Gateway Runner does:
	â€¢	Authenticates GitHub request
	â€¢	Calls Bamboo REST API:

/rest/api/latest/queue/PROJECT-PLAN


	â€¢	Passes version/tag to Bamboo
	â€¢	Starts the CI/CD pipeline

